# Docker commands

1. Docker basic commands
docker --help
docker --version

docker search 'image name'
docker pull 'imageName'
docker create 'containerId'
docker start 'containerId'
docker run 'imageName'

docker ps
docker ps -a
docker images

docker rm 'containerId'
docker rmi 'imageId'

2. Docker command after creating springBoot project

-- unruffled_tesla | container name

docker exec unruffled_tesla ls /tmp
docker cp target/rest-demo-docker.jar unruffled_tesla:/tmp
docker exec unruffled_tesla ls /tmp
docker commit unruffled_tesla robert/rest-demo-docker:v1
docker images
docker run robert/rest-demo-docker:v1
docker ps
docker commit --change='CMD ["java", "-jar", "/tmp/rest-demo-docker.jar"]' unruffled_tesla robert/rest-demo-docker:v2
docker images
docker run robert/rest-demo-docker:v2
docker run -p 8081:8081 robert/rest-demo-docker:v2
docker run -p 8070:8081 robert/rest-demo-docker:v2
java -jar target/rest-demo-docker.jar


3. To create a docker file to create images directly instead of creating manually evrytime

- Create a "Dockerfile" directly under project similar location of pom.xml
docker build -t robert/rest-demo-docker:v4 .
docker run -p 8078:8081 robert/rest-demo-docker:v3
